lem is challenging due to the limited diversity of facial expressions and poses in monocular videos, the absence of 3D observations leading to ambiguity in occluded parts, and the need to effectively integrate the strengths of SMPL-X and 3D Gaussian Splatting.\n\n**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**\nPrevious approaches either lack the ability to animate facial expressions and hand poses or require extensive 3D observations, which are not available in most casual videos. The problem has not been solved due to the complexity of handling limited data and the need for advanced techniques to integrate different modeling approaches.\n\n**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**\nThe proposed approach includes developing advanced data augmentation techniques, robust occlusion handling methods, and optimized hybrid representations. The methodology will involve training the hybrid model using a combination of real and synthesized data, and evaluating its performance on a variety of tasks. Expected outcomes include a more expressive 3D avatar that can be created from limited monocular video data, with improved handling of occlusions and better integration of SMPL-X and 3D Gaussian Splatting.", role='assistant', tool_calls=None, function_call=None, provider_specific_fields=None)'.
