**High-level summarized insight:**
Creating expressive whole-body 3D human avatars from short monocular videos is challenging due to limited diversity in facial expressions and poses and the absence of 3D observations. Addressing these issues requires innovative techniques in data augmentation, depth estimation, and hybrid representation. Leveraging my expertise in developing efficient and innovative models, I propose a novel approach that integrates advanced data augmentation, depth estimation, and enhanced connectivity between 3D Gaussians to create more expressive and realistic avatars.

**Here are the five core questions:**

**[Question 1] - What is the problem?**
How can we create an expressive whole-body 3D human avatar from a short monocular video that supports novel facial expressions, hand poses, and body poses?

**[Question 2] - Why is it interesting and important?**
Solving this problem will enable the creation of more realistic and expressive avatars for applications in virtual reality, augmented reality, and human-computer interaction. It will also advance the field of 3D human modeling and animation, leading to practical applications in entertainment, education, and healthcare.

**[Question 3] - Why is it hard?**
The limited diversity of facial expressions and poses in a short monocular video makes it difficult to create a fully expressive avatar. The absence of 3D observations leads to ambiguity in occluded parts, causing artifacts in animations. Existing volumetric avatars lack connectivity, and previous 3DGS-based works treat Gaussians as a point cloud without connectivity.

**[Question 4] - Why hasn't it been solved before?**
Previous approaches have focused on either enhancing the parametric model (SMPL-X) or improving the rendering capability (3DGS) but have not addressed the challenges of limited diversity and lack of 3D observations. The hybrid representation used in ExAvatar does not fully capture the connectivity between 3D Gaussians, leading to suboptimal results. My approach will integrate advanced data augmentation, depth estimation, and enhanced connectivity to overcome these limitations.

**[Question 5] - What are the key components of my approach and results?**
The proposed approach includes advanced data augmentation techniques to increase the diversity of facial expressions and poses, depth estimation methods to handle occlusions, and enhanced connectivity between 3D Gaussians to improve the hybrid representation. The methodology will be evaluated using a combination of synthetic and real-world datasets, with metrics such as visual quality, animation fidelity, and user satisfaction. Expected outcomes include a more expressive and realistic avatar that can be animated with novel facial expressions, hand poses, and body poses from a short monocular video.

