r learning.\n- **Handling Occlusions:** Address the challenge through depth estimation and inpainting techniques.\n\n#### 8. **Feasibility Assessment**\n- **Computational Resources:** Estimate the computational resources required.\n- **Time Requirements:** Estimate the time required for each phase of the project.\n\n#### 9. **Expected Outcomes**\n- **Avatar Quality:** Describe the expected improvements in the quality of the avatar's expressions and poses.\n- **Generalization:** Discuss the expected improvements in the avatar's ability to generalize to novel expressions and poses.\n\n#### 10. **Conclusion**\n- **Summary:** Summarize the key points of the research proposal.\n- **Impact:** Discuss the broader implications and potential applications of the research.\n\n#### 11. **References**\n- **Citations:** Include all relevant citations from the literature review and methodology sections.\n\n### Next Task\n\n**Task: Draft the Refined Research Proposal Document**\n\n**Objective:** To create a detailed and feasible research proposal document based on the refined methodology, datasets, evaluation metrics, and feasibility assessment.\n\n**Steps:**\n\n1. **Draft the Abstract and Introduction:**\n   - Write a concise abstract summarizing the research.\n   - Develop an introduction that sets the context and outlines the problem.\n\n2. **Draft the Literature Review:**\n   - Summarize existing work and identify gaps.\n\n3. **Draft the Methodology Section:**\n   - Detail the hybrid representation, data augmentation, and occlusion handling techniques.\n\n4. **Draft the Datasets Section:**\n   - Describe the datasets used for training and evaluation.\n   - Explain the process of synthetic data generation.\n\n5. **Draft the Evaluation Metrics Section:**\n   - Develop and describe new evaluation metrics.\n   - Explain how these metrics will be applied and measured.\n\n6. **Draft the Challenges and Solutions Section:**\n   - Revisit the challenges and provide detailed solutions.\n